{"title":"Combined feed","url":"https://leoshcn.github.io/feeds/all.xml","elements":[{"title":"Timon (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that conflicting traditions consider <b><a href=\"/wiki/Timon_(deacon)\" title=\"Timon (deacon)\">Timon</a></b> <i>(pictured)</i> to have served as bishop of either Bostra or Corinth, to have died by either fire or crucifixion, and to have died in either Corinth or Philippi?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Timon_(deacon)","retrieved":1776581785708},{"title":"OAP Bratislava (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that the manager of <b><a href=\"/wiki/OAP_Bratislava\" title=\"OAP Bratislava\">OAP Bratislava</a></b> was kept a secret from the public because he was Jewish?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/OAP_Bratislava","retrieved":1776581785709},{"title":"Hannah Spencer (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that <b><a href=\"/wiki/Hannah_Spencer\" title=\"Hannah Spencer\">Hannah Spencer</a></b> qualified as a plasterer in the same month that she became the first Green Party MP to win a UK by-election?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hannah_Spencer","retrieved":1776581785710},{"title":"Council of Censors (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that Pennsylvania's 1776 constitution created the <b><a href=\"/wiki/Council_of_Censors\" title=\"Council of Censors\">Council of Censors</a></b>, one of the earliest American institutions expressly charged with enforcing a written constitution against <a href=\"/wiki/Ordinary_law\" title=\"Ordinary law\">ordinary laws</a>?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Council_of_Censors","retrieved":1776581785712},{"title":"John Walsh (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that <b><a href=\"/wiki/John_Walsh_(dentist)\" title=\"John Walsh (dentist)\">John Walsh</a></b> invented the high-speed dental drill after conducting hearing tests on returned servicemen?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_Walsh_(dentist)","retrieved":1776581785714},{"ti